						               													<description>From the publisher:&amp;#10;Welcome to the world of Two Hour Wargames!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Chain Reaction 2015 is an introduction to Two Hour Wargames. It&amp;rsquo;s a complete game &amp;ndash; not a teaser &amp;ndash; and is free. Chain Reaction 2015 is a set of man-to-man combat rules that can be played in a variety of periods and with any figures you may already have.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Chain Reaction 2015, like all THW games, can be played solo, cooperatively &amp;ndash; all players on the same side &amp;ndash; or competitively &amp;ndash; head to head. Inside you&amp;rsquo;ll find:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The current Reaction System, used in all Two Hour Wargames, that allows you to learn one set of mechanics to play a variety of periods.&amp;#10;     Quick game mechanics that yield realistic shooting and melee results.  &amp;#10;     Three scenarios that can be played over and over with no two games ever being the same.&amp;#10;     Character advancement based on your success in each game.&amp;#10;     An easy to use Campaign system that generates your next game based on how well you&amp;rsquo;ve done.&amp;#10;     Ways to generate your characters and your opponents &amp;ndash; Police, Gangers, Militia, Guerillas, and Military.&amp;#10;     All this and more&amp;hellip;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Chain Reaction 2015 lets you to learn the current version of the Reaction System used by THW without spending a dime. While our counterpart Swordplay is about hand-to-hand combat with sword and shield, Chain Reaction 2015 is about modern firearms.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Chain Reaction 2015 gives you a chance to see if you like the Reaction System, before trying one of our period specific games. Think of Chain Reaction 2015 as a preview of our other period specific games like 5150: Star Army, All Things Zombie &amp;ndash; Final Fade Out, and NUTS!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Chain Reaction is updated every few years in line with the new editions of Two Hour Wargames other rules.  Updates so far have been published in 2018 and 2020.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
